  "body": "I am a bit confused about the following formula in YP.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper/blob/630ed566d4d147124783bbad9d9d3aa5c3522e2b/Paper.tex#L2588\r\n\r\nSpecifically, (In appendix __H.2. Instruction Set.__) after evaluating a CALL opcode, the available gas is defined by the blue circled formula.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14835483/153975674-7adbe1a3-ac90-45f5-91d7-cd36fe56c059.png)\r\n\r\nBased on my understanding, `\\mu_g` denotes the available gas before evaluating the CALL opcode, `g^'` denotes the available gas of the callee function, and `\\mu_g^'` denotes the available gas after evaluating the CALL opcode. Please kindly correct me if I made it wrong.\r\n\r\nI am then a bit confused why it is an addition. I feel the correct version may be the black circled formula as follows. Here I only consider the case of the call being successfully processed, i.e., not the case of insufficient balance or exceeded call depth.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14835483/153976558-01feabc9-fede-4f03-99e7-4e46bf23ef66.png)\r\n\r\nBesides, I failed to find the definition of the yellow circled `g`. \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14835483/153977122-1223977c-e317-4e39-8754-0881eb9baf7d.png)\r\n\r\nI am not sure whether I understand it correctly. It would be very appreciated if anyone can shed some light on this.\r\n\r\nMany thanks!\r\n",
